  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> <strong>loved\n        him...</strong></font><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p><font>The line occurs twice in Shakespeare,\n        in II King Henry IV (3.2.42) and Macbeth (4.3.18). The\n        context of the latter suits the poem slightly better, for\n        it fits the reference to Joyce; in the fromer death is\n        caused by arrows, which may refer to the St. Sebastian\n        painting.</font></p>\n<p><font><em>reference topics</em></font></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td>Shakespeare and \"Burbank\"</td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Portrait and \"Burbank\"</td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank.htm\">Burbank</a>\n                and The Beautiful Dream</td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Burbank and Bleistein</td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><font>back to \"Burbank\" </font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "loved him... The line occurs twice in Shakespeare, in II King Henry IV (3.2.42) and Macbeth (4.3.18). The context of the latter suits the poem slightly better, for it fits the reference to Joyce; in the fromer death is caused by arrows, which may refer to the St. Sebastian painting. reference topics Shakespeare and \"Burbank\" Portrait and \"Burbank\" Burbank and The Beautiful Dream Burbank and Bleistein back to \"Burbank\"",
